  "summary": "kuaishou@99.9.10 exfiltrates installer host identity to ngrok tunnel on install",
  "details": "The package's `prepare` lifecycle script runs index.js at install time, which collects the installer's username, current working directory / INIT_CWD, hostname, and non-internal IPv4 address, then POSTs a JSON payload containing these fields to a hardcoded attacker-controlled endpoint at https://crabbing-thong-overhung.ngrok-free.dev. The package has version 99.9.10 and no functional code beyond the beacon, consistent with a dependency-confusion / typosquat reconnaissance probe against internal package names.",
